title: Winning By Losing Less
text: What is surprising is that the S&P 500 Low Volatility Index outperformed the benchmark by almost 3%, gaining 26% over the same period.

title: Growth Versus Value – Has The Tide Turned?
text: Value stocks have been leading growth since early in October and some value managers are wondering whether this is a change in the major trend. Tom Aspray shares his analysis of the growth-value ratio and whether there is a change to the longer term trend.

title: Investing Insights: Bank Dividend Stocks and Choosing Target-Date Funds
text: In this week’s podcast, equity analyst Eric Compton highlights bank dividends, Vanguard’s Rich Powers discusses what drives fund flows into ETFs, equity analyst Scott Pope explains what makes United Rentals attractive, Jeff Holt provides guidance on choosing the right target-date fund, and analyst Eric Jacobson shares our favorite core plus bond fonds.

title: This under-the-radar market trend suggests new record highs through December
text: CFRA's Sam Stovall builds a positive case on stocks based on a historical pattern dating back to WWII.
